extractProofValue(bytes32,bytes,RLPReade.details: Validates a Merkle-Patricia-Trie proof.      If the proof proves the inclusion of some key-value pair in the      trie, the value is returned. Otherwise, i.e. if the proof proves      the exclusion of a key from the trie, an empty byte array is      returned.

params.path: is the key of the node whose inclusion/exclusion we are        proving.
params.rootHash: is the Keccak-256 hash of the root node of the MPT.
params.stack: is the stack of MPT nodes (starting with the root) that        need to be traversed during verification.

returns.value: whose inclusion is proved or an empty byte array for         a proof of exclusion
